thread.title_full: Carlisle routs Saydel for big win; hosts Chariton next

author: desmoinesregister.com
title: Carlisle routs Saydel for big win; hosts Chariton next
text:
Buy Photo Carlisle Community Schools (Photo: The Register) Buy Photo
CONNECT TWEET The Carlisle football team proved too much for a Saydel program searching for its second win of the season as the Wildcats won 54-7 on Oct. 9.
Senior Andrew Burrnett led the Wildcat offense with 154 yards rushing on 13 attempts for two touchdowns. His longest run came from 49 yards out. Other players picking up rushing touchdowns were senior quarterback Jordan Pierce (2), and seniors Chase Shanahan and Peyton Stephens with one apiece.
Pierce thew just two passes on the night, completing both, totaling 57 yards and one touchdown. junior Dallas Wright hauled in that one touchdown, his only reception of the night for 33 yards.
On defense, senior Joe Crowley recorded a team-high six-and-a-half tackles (five solo, three assisted).
Carlisle (4-3), will host Chariton (5-2) Friday for Senior Nigh. Chariton is coming off a 41-26 victory over Knoxville. Senior wide receiver and Iowa commit T.J. Hockenson's became the state's all-time leader in career receiving touchdowns with 47 that night. The record was previously held by Pleasantville's Grant McGraw, who caught 46 touchdown passes during his career from 1992-95.
The game is scheduled to start at 7:30 p.m.
